Hub: a multiport repeater
Repeater:
  - Receives a digital signal
  - Amplifies Signal
  - Broadcasts signal out to other ports
  
 Network Segmentation:
  - Breaking up a large network into smaller domains
 
 WLAN Controller :
  - Wireless LAN controller manages wireless Access Points and frames
  
  VLAN: 
    - Breaks up broadcast domains on a layer 2 network
    
 OSI Model:
 
 7 layers divided into 2 groups, the top three layers defines how the applications will communicate with each other as well as users
 Bottom 4 layers defines how data is transferred end to end.
 
 
